quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  4,92,"But never should a believer kill another believer, unless accidentally. Yet anyone who accidentally kills a believer, then the<i class=",footnotes:1:Literally 'a neck'.,footnotes:2:Unless they waive it as charity.,footnotes:3:Literally ‘a neck’.,footnotes:4:Literally ‘a neck’.
  4,93,"But whoever kills a believer intentionally—then his repayment is Hell, abiding therein, and upon him is Allah’s wrath and He has cursed him and has prepared for him a great punishment."
  4,94,"O you who have attained faith, when you travel<i class=""s"">(to strive) </i>in the way of Allah, then <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza, Al Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…then you shall ascertain (the truth).”</span>,footnotes:2:This means greeting with the salutation of peace by saying: ‘Peace be upon you.’”,footnotes:3:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Amer, Hamza, Abu Ja’far and Khalaf read it as: “And do not say to anyone who offers to surrender to you, “You are not…”</span>,footnotes:4:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Wardan read it as: “You are not granted security,”</span>,footnotes:5:The same word, <i>maghanem,</i> is used for ‘spoils of war’.
